              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">SoftBank eyes $500 million investment in AI robotics startup</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">SoftBank Group is planning a <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-29-01-2025-h2-2-500-million-funding-round" target="_blank">$500 million funding round</a> for Skild AI, a Pittsburgh-based software startup. Founded by Carnegie Mellon professors and former Meta AI researchers, the company develops software that enables robots to perform complex tasks. The startup has attracted many big investors, with Jeff Bezos, Amazon, Lightspeed Venture Partners, and Sequoia Capital already on board. Softbank’s planned investment would raise Skild AI’s valuation to $4 billion, a significant jump from its $1.5 billion valuation last year.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
